theorem Topology.dense_of_interior_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : interior (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X)) :
    Dense (A : Set X) := by
  -- First, show that `closure A = univ`.
  have h_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    -- Since `interior A = univ`, and `interior A ⊆ closure A`,
    -- the desired inclusion follows immediately.
    have : (interior (A : Set X) : Set X) ⊆ closure A := subset_closure
    simpa [h] using this
  have h_eq : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    -- The reverse inclusion is trivial.
    have h_superset : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      intro _ _; simp
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm h_superset h_subset
  -- Conclude density from the description of dense sets via closure.
  simpa [h_eq] using
    (dense_iff_closure_eq (s := (A : Set X))).2 h_eq

theorem Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  -- We prove the equality by showing mutual inclusions.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- `interior` is monotone, so it suffices to have an inclusion between
    -- the underlying sets.
    have h_closure_subset : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
      -- `interior (closure A)` is contained in `closure A` by definition;
      -- taking closures preserves this inclusion.
      have h₁ : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      exact closure_minimal h₁ isClosed_closure
    -- Apply the monotonicity of `interior`.
    exact interior_mono h_closure_subset
  ·
    -- The other inclusion follows from the fact that every set is contained
    -- in the closure of itself, together with monotonicity of `interior`.
    have h_subset : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure A)) := subset_closure
    -- Using `interior_mono` and the fact that `interior (interior (closure A))`
    -- is just `interior (closure A)`, we obtain the desired inclusion.
    simpa [interior_interior] using interior_mono h_subset

theorem Topology.interior_inter_eq_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen A) (hB : IsOpen B) :
    interior (A ∩ B : Set X) = A ∩ B := by
  simpa using (IsOpen.inter hA hB).interior_eq
